\@writefile{toc}{\contentsline {paragraph}{Intrinsic Metric 3: Visual Grounding Score (VGS).}{2}{section*.3}\protected@file@percent }
\@writefile{toc}{\contentsline {paragraph}{Evaluation methodology: LLM-as-Judge for feedback quality.}{2}{section*.4}\protected@file@percent }
\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces \texttt  {\textbf  {\textcolor {blue}{[1 points]}}} Intrinsic and extrinsic metrics. Intrinsic metrics (PC Recall, FSR, VGS) computed from 8B per-example outputs on H3 evaluation set (N=108; 61 partially correct, 47 incorrect). Extrinsic metrics (Verdict, Match\%, SoftM\%) from H1/H2 evaluation (N=50 per condition). PC Recall = partially-correct recall; FSR = feedback suppression rate (lower is better); VGS = visual grounding score, factual errors only; Verdict = three-class accuracy; Match\% = LLM-as-Judge strict match; SoftM\% = Match + Partial. 32B intrinsic metrics marked --- (per-example outputs unavailable). Routing combines C1 verdict with C4 feedback at no additional inference cost.}}{3}{table.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:intrinsic}{{1}{3}{\points {1} Intrinsic and extrinsic metrics. Intrinsic metrics (PC Recall, FSR, VGS) computed from 8B per-example outputs on H3 evaluation set (N=108; 61 partially correct, 47 incorrect). Extrinsic metrics (Verdict, Match\%, SoftM\%) from H1/H2 evaluation (N=50 per condition). PC Recall = partially-correct recall; FSR = feedback suppression rate (lower is better); VGS = visual grounding score, factual errors only; Verdict = three-class accuracy; Match\% = LLM-as-Judge strict match; SoftM\% = Match + Partial. 32B intrinsic metrics marked --- (per-example outputs unavailable). Routing combines C1 verdict with C4 feedback at no additional inference cost}{table.1}{}}
